More than 500 exponents and representatives of international organizations from about 80 countries are participating as of Tuesday in the 7th INTERPOL Global Conference on Human Trafficking and Migrant Smuggling. The annual meeting taking place in Buenos Aires until Wednesday, September 11, welcomes members of law enforcement agencies and specialized units engaged in border security and combating crimes related to human trafficking, migrant smuggling and crimes against children. Academics and experts will analyze in depth through panels and roundtables current and sensitive issues in efforts to fight this global problem, with particular attention on data analysis and financial flows. The meeting is organized by the Argentine Federal Police and the Ministry of Security in cooperation with the INTERPOL Foundation for a Safer World and follows on from the previous 2018 edition, held in Nigeria, Abuja.